  "text": "f . Eq. (30) then reveals thatf \u03c0 = f \u03c0 in the chiral limit, which result is well-known from the axial anomaly analysis. Although the chiral limit formula (30) can be applied without reservations only to pions, it is customary to write the amplitudes for \u03b7 8 , \u03b7 0 \u2192 \u03b3\u03b3 in the same form as [CITATION_1] , defining thereby the \u03b3\u03b3-decay constantsf \u03b7 8 andf \u03b7 0 :",
